items.title: Jubilant FoodWorks: India business picking up, valuation expensive

items.title: Trump’s plans to boost LNG will help India’s buyers, Gail says
items.description: Indian imports of the fuel peaked in 2020, and have struggled to rebound as prices surged following Russia’s invasion of Ukraine in 2022.

items.title: Blackstone, Brookfield, Warburg Pincus in talks for majority stake in Gland Pharma, says report
items.description: The deal between the three global private equity majors and China’s Shanghai Fosun Pharma - which owns a majority stake in the company - is likely to value the company at around $3 billion, the report added.

items.title: Tata Steel likely to tap bond market after near 1-year hiatus; stock up 3%
items.description: Tata Steel is likely to raise around Rs 3,000 crore($345.6 million) through this bond issue and will likely complete the issue before the end of this month

items.title: Rashmi Saluja, Executive Chairperson, ceases to be a director of Religare Enterprises
items.description: Religare Enterprises cited a report by the Scrutinizer, which said that 97% votes were cast against the resolution seeking reappointment of Rashmi Saluja on the board of REL, dated February 7.

items.title: Exclusive | India-Bhutan renew talks for hydropower project
items.description: Raj Kumar Chaudhary, CMD, NHPC Ltd told Moneycontrol that other than its operational hydropower capacity of 6,571 MW, the company has an additional  9,314 MW of hydro capacities under construction.

items.title: M&M Finance approves Rs 3,000 crore rights issue, sees 'tremendous growth opportunity' in consumption
items.description: The NBFC said it sees 'tremendous growth opportunity' with regard to India’s domestic consumption growth, going forward, and the capital raise will support the company's growth aspirations for next few years.
